reviews.review_text: Recording You do an outstanding job of recording shows.  I like the sound so much better then A sound board. Not just this recording but all of your recordings.      Love the mind left body jam.  seeing as so many of us left our bodys.

Improv: Thanks for anwering that or  are you confusing this jam with another? Yes, I noticed too a distinct chord progression there! So I looked for someone (yours) to identity it. However, I think it was something else because they either did that so-called "Mind left Body" thing on one of the other nights or at before April Fool's and later at one of the Community Th. shows after Halloween in Berkeley or am I all screwed up?

     I have to double check some more having covered those shows semi-recently; you see I listen to the 211 shows I attended in reverse chronological order. (Not that you should give a damn: while I sit here reading science or doing e-mail etc., i.e. ("whistle while you work, Hitler was a Jerk, Mussolini - obscene rhyme"))!
       But besides whatever we might call the improvisational jam (not space since there's no air out there) it was definitely a decent show; like someone else said: "that prior to New Year's was better than New Year's itself", since we got spoiled the previous years!

     Augy

     San Diego
Best Aud source Great sound in the room at the Civic.  This is the best source of a few nice ones.
